[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m[[0m[39mINFO[0m[1;39m][0m[39m Finished at: [0m[1;36m2025[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m12[0m[39m-23T[0m[1;92m05:52:51[0m[39mZ[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m[[0m[39mINFO[0m[1;39m][0m[39m ------------------------------------------------------------------------[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m[[0m[39mERROR[0m[1;39m][0m[39m Failed to execute goal org.apache.maven.plugins:maven-co[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [33m...[0m[39m [0m[1;39m[[0m[39mTRUNCATED[0m[1;39m][0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===[0m[33mIssue[0m[39m===[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mERROR: libFuzzer: timeout[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA libFuzzer run terminated with an “ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout” message. During fuzz[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtesting, the fuzzing engine exceeded its allotted execution time for a test case or[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverall campaign, causing the process to abort with a timeout error.[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Issue Overview  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  The fuzzing session ended prematurely because libFuzzer detected that a specified[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtime limit had been surpassed. Rather than completing its normal probing of the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtarget code, the fuzzer exited with a timeout notification.[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Vulnerability Type  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  No explicit vulnerability type [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., memory corruption, out-of-bounds access[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmentioned; the error reflects a test execution limitation rather than a direct [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msecurity flaw.[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Important Observations and Findings  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The fuzzer harness acted as the entry point to the code under test. Although it[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtriggered the timeout, it is not itself the root cause.  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • A timeout indicates that one or more inputs caused execution to run longer than[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe configured threshold.  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The issue may reveal performance bottlenecks or infinite loops in the target [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcode, which can manifest as a denial-of-service condition under fuzzing.  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The exact point of hanging or prolonged execution is not logged in the error [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmessage, so further instrumentation or debug logging may be required to pinpoint [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhere time was spent.[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Code Areas for Investigation  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. Fuzzer Entry Point [0m[1;39m([0m[39mHarness[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Confirm that the harness correctly initializes and tears down any state or [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthreads.  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Ensure it does not suppress or delay termination signals sent by libFuzzer. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. Long-Running Code Paths  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Review loops, recursion, or blocking calls [0m[1;39m([0m[39mI/O, synchronization primitives[0m[1;39m)[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min the functions exercised by fuzz inputs.  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Look for cases where a guard condition or timeout check is missing.  [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. Resource Management  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Examine allocations, deallocations, and potential contention on shared data.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Check for network or file operations that may stall.  [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. Configuration and Flags  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Inspect fuzzing parameters [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., –timeout, –max_total_time[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to confirm they[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39malign with expected test durations.  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Verify that no unintended flags are extending or restricting execution time [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min a way that masks the underlying behavior.[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mBy reviewing the harness, target functions, and fuzzing configuration, developers [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcan obtain a more complete view of why the timeout occurred and identify the code [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mregions responsible for prolonged execution.[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<issue>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mERROR: libFuzzer: timeout[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95missue[0m[39m>[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Analysis [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Analysis Report[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Relevant Code Snippets[0m                                                           [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m197[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpassword.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m207[0m[39m:     * @throws IOException in case of a file reading or parsing error[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m208[0m[39m:     * [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m209[0m[39m:     * @deprecated use [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m@link Loader#[0m[1;35mloadPDF[0m[1;39m([0m[39mFile[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m instead[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m210[0m[39m:     *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m211[0m[39m:    @Deprecated[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m212[0m[39m:    public static PDDocument [0m[1;35mload[0m[1;39m([0m[39mFile file[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m throws IOException[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m213[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m214[0m[39m:        return [0m[1;35mLoader.loadPDF[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfile[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m215[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m216[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m217[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m218[0m[39m:     * Parses a PDF. Unrestricted main memory will be used for buffering PDF [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstreams.[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m219[0m[39m:     * [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m226[0m[39m:     * @throws IOException in case of a file reading or parsing error[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m227[0m[39m:     * [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m228[0m[39m:     * @deprecated use [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m@link Loader#[0m[1;35mloadPDF[0m[1;39m([0m[39mFile, String[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m instead[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m229[0m[39m:     *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m230[0m[39m:    @Deprecated[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m231[0m[39m:    public static PDDocument [0m[1;35mload[0m[1;39m([0m[39mFile file, String password[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m throws [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mIOException[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m232[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m233[0m[39m:        return [0m[1;35mLoader.loadPDF[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfile, password[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m234[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m236[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTo prevent libFuzzer timeouts caused by pathological inputs that force unbounded [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mscanning or near‐infinite loops in the parser, we will introduce strict, bounded [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msearch ranges for both PDF/FDF header detection and for backward “startxref” [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlookup, and ensure all whitespace‐skipping loops bail out on EOF. This preserves [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexisting parsing logic for well‐formed PDFs while capping worst‐case execution time[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mon malformed or crafted inputs.[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Introduce configurable “lookup range” constants and fields[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • In COSParser, define:[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - private static final int DEFAULT_[0m[1;33mHEAD[0m[39mER_LOOKUP = [0m[1;36m2048[0m[39m;[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - public static final String SYSPROP_[0m[1;33mHEAD[0m[39mER_LOOKUP = [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m"org.apache.pdfbox.pdfparser.headerLookupRange"[0m[39m;[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - private int headerLookupBytes = DEFAULT_[0m[1;33mHEAD[0m[39mER_LOOKUP;[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • In [0m[1;35minit[0m[1;39m([0m[39m…[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround where EOF-lookup is configured[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, read [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mSYSPROP_[0m[1;33mHEAD[0m[39mER_LOOKUP, parse and clamp to a sensible minimum [0m[1;39m([0m[39m>[0m[1;36m16[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, assigning to [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheaderLookupBytes.[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • This mirrors the existing EOF lookup‐range logic but applies to header [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mscanning.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Bound [0m[1;35mparsePDFHeader[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and [0m[1;35mparseFDFHeader[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to headerLookupBytes[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • Replace their unbounded loops:[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Before reading any bytes, compute int maxBytes = [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mint[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35mMath.min[0m[1;39m([0m[39mheaderLookupBytes, [0m[1;35msource.length[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Loop at most maxBytes times when scanning for the “%PDF-” [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor “%FDF-”[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmarker.[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - On each iteration, read one byte; if it matches the next byte in the marker,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39madvance; on mismatch, reset the match state; continue until either the full marker [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmatches [0m[1;39m([0m[39mreturn true[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m or the byte‐count limit is reached [0m[1;39m([0m[39mreturn false[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • This ensures that even if the test data lacks the marker or is huge, we will [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstop after headerLookupBytes, bounding runtime.[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Enforce EOF breaks in low‐level loops[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • In [0m[1;35mBaseParser.skipSpaces[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mand any similar loops that read until [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnon‐whitespace[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, before calling source.read or source.peek, check [0m[1;35msource.read[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m < [0m[1;36m0[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mor [0m[1;35mpeek[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m==[0m[1;36m-1[0m[39m, then break out. This prevents hanging when fuzz inputs end with [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mendless whitespace or malformed streams.[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • Confirm [0m[1;35mreadNextToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and other byte‐driven loops similarly exit on EOF.[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Keep “startxref” backward search bounded by readTrailBytes[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • The existing [0m[1;35mgetStartxrefOffset[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m uses DEFAULT_TRAIL_BYTECOUNT [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m2048[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreadTrailBytes; ensure readTrailBytes remains at a modest default to bound backward[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mscanning.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • No change needed here, except to document that the default is already bounded.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. No modifications to harness, fuzz logic, or external dependencies[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • All changes are confined to parser classes.[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • Existing parsing behavior for valid, well‐formed PDFs [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwith headers in the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfirst ~[0m[1;36m2[0m[39m KB and trailers in the last ~[0m[1;36m2[0m[39m KB[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m remains identical.[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • Tests covering standard PDFs will continue to pass; malformed inputs now [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfast‐fail header detection and proceed to lenient fallback or throw, rather than [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhung loops.[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mRationale[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m– By limiting header scanning to a few kilobytes, we still adhere to PDF [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mspecification [0m[1;39m([0m[39mheader must appear at file start[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and protect against [0m[1;35mO[0m[1;39m([0m[39mN[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m or [0m[1;35mO[0m[1;39m([0m[39mN²[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbehavior on large/malformed fuzzed inputs.  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m– Ensuring skipSpaces and similar loops break on EOF stops potential infinite loops[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhen whitespace isn’t followed by expected tokens.  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m– The existing bounded trailer lookup avoids unbounded backward scans.  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m– These measures cap parser runtime per input, preventing libFuzzer timeouts [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwithout degrading correctness for valid PDFs.[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPotential Side Effects & Mitigation[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m– Very large valid PDFs where the header appears beyond the first headerLookupBytes[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39munlikely per spec[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m may fail header detection; however, the parser falls back to [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mFDF header or lenient mode and ultimately rebuilds via bruteForceParser if lenient.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m– Developers can override SYSPROP_[0m[1;33mHEAD[0m[39mER_LOOKUP to increase the search window if [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnecessary.[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mCode References[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m– [0m[1;35minit[0m[1;39m([0m[39m…[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m in COSParser for EOF lookup range: uses SYSPROP_EOFLOOKUPRANGE and [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mDEFAULT_TRAIL_BYTECOUNT.  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m– [0m[1;35mparsePDFHeader[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[35m/[0m[95mparseFDFHeader[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m in COSParser around lines [0m[1;36m157[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m166[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m200[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m300[0m[39m.  [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m– [0m[1;35mskipSpaces[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m in BaseParser [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m300[0m[39m in BaseParser.java[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue reported by the fuzzing harness was a timeout in libFuzzer when [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexercising PDFBox parsing code [0m[1;39m([0m[39m“ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout”[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. In response, a patch [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwas proposed that removes several constructors in `COSParser`, adds two new [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheader‐scanning methods [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;35mparsePDFHeader[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;35mparseFDFHeader[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, and inserts a [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnew whitespace‐skipping method [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;35mskipSpaces[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m into `BaseParser`. After applying [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe patch, the code fails to compile with dozens of “illegal start of expression” [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand “class, interface, or enum expected” errors in `BaseParser.java`, indicating [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat the patch mis-placed code fragments [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbraces, method declarations, or context[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand broke the overall class structure.[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – A fuzzing run against PDFBox triggered a libFuzzer timeout, meaning the target[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparser did not complete within the allotted time.  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – No stack trace or specific PDF input was provided; the only observable symptom[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwas the timeout exit.[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Important Observations  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – The timeout suggests that PDF parsing routines [0m[1;39m([0m[39mprobably in `COSParser` or [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`BaseParser`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m are taking unexpectedly long on certain inputs.  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – No compilation or runtime errors were shown before the patch; the codebase [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcompiled and ran normally under non-fuzzing conditions.[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   The patch makes three main changes:[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. In `COSParser.java`:  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      • Deletes two existing constructors [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe no-arg and encrypted constructors[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      • Adds a private `[0m[1;35mparsePDFHeader[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method that reads up to [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`headerLookupRange` bytes from `source` looking for the standard PDF file header.  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      • Adds a private `[0m[1;35mparseFDFHeader[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method that does the same for FDF files. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. In `BaseParser.java`:  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      • After a snippet that breaks out on encountering ‘>’, removes an `else if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mc[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m== [0m[32m'/'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m … [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m` block.  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      • Inserts a new protected method `[0m[1;35mskipSpaces[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` which repeatedly reads bytes,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mskips known whitespace [0m[1;39m([0m[39mspace, line feed, carriage return, tab, form feed, NUL[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mupon encountering a non-whitespace byte, seeks back one position.[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c. Context lines suggest the insertions were intended around line [0m[1;36m292[0m[39m in [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`BaseParser.java`.[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Patch Result  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – Compilation fails in `BaseParser.java` with a cascade of “illegal start of [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexpression” and “class, interface, or enum expected” errors [0m[1;39m([0m[39mover [0m[1;36m100[0m[39m errors[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – The errors indicate that the `[0m[1;35mskipSpaces[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method declaration and possibly [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe earlier bracket modifications have been placed inside another method or outside[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe class body, violating Java syntax.  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – The build log pinpoints the first error at line [0m[1;36m295[0m[39m, column [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m, implying that [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe code structure around that line no longer matches a valid class or method [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlayout.[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – Verify the opening and closing braces in `BaseParser.java` around line [0m[1;36m292[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m300[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto ensure that the new method is declared at the class level, not nested inside [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39manother method or outside the class.  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – Check that the context lines used by the patch [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe surrounding `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mc == [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m'>'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` block and its closing brace[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m correctly match the actual source, so the [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minsertion point did not shift.  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – In `COSParser.java`, confirm that constructors removed by the patch aren’t [0m    [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – Examine whether additional imports [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g. `StandardCharsets`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m or field [0m         [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1374[0m[39m:            throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1375[0m[39m:                    [0m[32m"Generation Number '"[0m[39m + retval + [0m[32m"' has more than 5 digits[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mor is negative"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1376[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1377[0m[39m:        return retval;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1378[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1379[0m[39m:    [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1380[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1381[0m[39m:     * This will read an integer from the stream.[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1382[0m[39m:     *[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1383[0m[39m:     * @return The integer that was read from the stream.[0m                      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1385[0m[39m:     * @throws IOException If there is an error reading from the stream.[0m       [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1387[0m[39m:    protected int [0m[1;35mreadInt[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m throws IOException[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1388[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1389[0m[39m:        [0m[1;35mskipSpaces[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1390[0m[39m:        int retval = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1391[0m[39m:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1392[0m[39m:        StringBuilder intBuffer = [0m[1;35mreadStringNumber[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1393[0m[39m:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1394[0m[39m:        try[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1395[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1396[0m[39m:            retval = [0m[1;35mInteger.parseInt[0m[1;39m([0m[39m [0m[1;35mintBuffer.toString[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1397[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1398[0m[39m:        [0m[1;35mcatch[0m[1;39m([0m[39m NumberFormatException e [0m[1;39m)[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1399[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1400[0m[39m:            [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35msource.rewind[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mintBuffer.toString[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.getBytes[0m[1;39m([0m[39mStandardCharsets.ISO_8859_1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.length[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/BaseParser.jav[0m[1;92ma:1319[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1343[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1319[0m[39m:    protected void [0m[1;35mskipSpaces[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m throws IOException[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1320[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1321[0m[39m:        int c = [0m[1;35msource.read[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1322[0m[39m:        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m[1;36m37[0m[39m is the % character, a comment[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1323[0m[39m:        [0m[1;35mwhile[0m[1;39m([0m[39m [0m[1;35misWhitespace[0m[1;39m([0m[39mc[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m || c == [0m[1;36m37[0m[1;39m)[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1324[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1325[0m[39m:            if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m c == [0m[1;36m37[0m[39m [0m[1;39m)[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1326[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1327[0m[39m:                [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m skip past the comment section[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1328[0m[39m:                c = [0m[1;35msource.read[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1329[0m[39m:                [0m[1;35mwhile[0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35misEOL[0m[1;39m([0m[39mc[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m && c != [0m[1;36m-1[0m[1;39m)[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1330[0m[39m:                [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1331[0m[39m:                    c = [0m[1;35msource.read[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1332[0m[39m:                [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1333[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1334[0m[39m:            else[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1335[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1336[0m[39m:                c = [0m[1;35msource.read[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1337[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1338[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1339[0m[39m:        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mc != [0m[1;36m-1[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1340[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1341[0m[39m:            [0m[1;35msource.rewind[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1342[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1343[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Summary of Root Causes[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In BaseParser.java, the last patch erroneously inserted a full `[0m[1;35mskipSpaces[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmethod declaration inside the body of `[0m[1;35mparseCOSDictionary[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`. This breaks the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmethod/class-level brace structure, leading to “illegal start of expression” and [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m“class, interface, or enum expected” errors.[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In BaseParser.java, the original `else if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mc == [0m[32m'/'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m … [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m` block in [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`parseCOSDictionary` was removed, further misaligning braces and changing parser [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlogic.[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In COSParser.java, the javadoc closing delimiter [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`*[0m[35m/[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m for the removed [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconstructors was deleted, so the new `[0m[1;35mparsePDFHeader[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;35mparseFDFHeader[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msignatures are interpreted inside an unclosed comment, also disrupting the class [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstructure.[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. High-Level Fix Steps[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   A. Restore parseCOSDictionary in BaseParser.java[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. Locate the `[0m[1;35mparseCOSDictionary[0m[1;39m([0m[39mboolean isDirect[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m281[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. Remove the mistakenly inserted `protected void [0m[1;35mskipSpaces[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m … [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m` block [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat was placed between the `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mc == [0m[32m'>'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `else [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m … [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m` branches.[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. Restore the original `else if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mc == [0m[32m'/'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m … [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m` block exactly as it was in[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe initial code, including its opening/closing braces and call to [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mparseCOSDictionaryNameValuePair[0m[1;39m([0m[39mobj[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. Ensure that within `parseCOSDictionary`:[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         - All braces match: the `while [0m[1;39m([0m[39mtrue[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m … [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m` loop has one opening and one [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mclosing brace.[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         - Only calls to `[0m[1;35mskipSpaces[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` remain inside the method [0m[1;39m([0m[39mno nested method [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeclarations[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m. Confirm that the single, correct `[0m[1;35mskipSpaces[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` definition remains in its [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moriginal location [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m1319[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and remove any duplicate definitions.[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   B. Repair COSParser.java Javadoc and Method Placement[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. Find the removed no-arg and encrypted constructors in `COSParser.java` [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39maround lines [0m[1;36m147[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m180[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. Re-insert or retain the closing `*[0m[35m/[0m[39m` of the javadoc comment that preceded [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe first constructor, so that any subsequent methods are parsed correctly.[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         - Option A: If retaining the constructor comment, append `*[0m[35m/[0m[39m` before the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfirst `[0m[1;35mparsePDFHeader[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` declaration.[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         - Option B: Remove the entire constructor javadoc block since the [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconstructors themselves are deleted, avoiding dangling comment markers.[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. Move the two new methods [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;35mparsePDFHeader[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;35mparseFDFHeader[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to a [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlogical location at class scope—preferably after existing parsing helper methods [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbut before the final closing `[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m` of `COSParser`.[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. Add appropriate small javadocs or inline comments for these methods, [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mensuring each is preceded and followed by valid comment delimiters.[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m. If not already present, add the import `import [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mjava.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;` at the top of the file.[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m. Verify all opening/closing braces in `COSParser.java` are balanced and [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat the class ends with exactly one closing brace.[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Preservation of Existing Logic[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - By restoring the original `else if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mc == [0m[32m'/'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` block, dictionary parsing [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbehavior remains unchanged, preserving backward compatibility.[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The single `[0m[1;35mskipSpaces[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` helper is retained in one place, so all callers [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontinue to function, and no existing tests will break.[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The new header‐scanning methods in `COSParser` stay available for eventual [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtimeout mitigation but are correctly placed so they compile.[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Justification[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Moving the duplicate `[0m[1;35mskipSpaces[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` back to its canonical location and [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrestoring the dictionary-naming logic fixes the malformed structure, resolving [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhundreds of compile errors without altering fuzzer harness code or external [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdependencies.[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Properly closing javadoc in `COSParser` ensures new methods are recognized as [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcode, not comment.[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This approach minimially patches only the intended parser files, retains [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexisting functionality, and addresses the fuzz‐reported timeout once compiled.[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Post-Patch Validation[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Rebuild the project to confirm no syntax errors in `BaseParser.java` or [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`COSParser.java`.[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Run existing unit and integration tests to ensure parsing behavior is [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munchanged.[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Reinvoke libFuzzer to verify the timeout issue persists; later iterations can [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtune header‐scan logic without structural issues.[0m                                   [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===[0m[33mIssue[0m[39m===[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mERROR: libFuzzer: timeout[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe project’s PDF parsing component triggered a libFuzzer timeout during fuzz [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtesting. In response, a contributor attempted to refactor the `COSParser` class by [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mremoving its public constructors and adding two new private [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmethods—`[0m[1;35mparsePDFHeader[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;35mparseFDFHeader[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`—to scan for file headers in a [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmore controlled way. After applying the patch, the build failed with multiple [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcompilation errors: duplicate method definitions, missing symbol errors for a new [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfield [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`headerLookupRange`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, and broken constructor calls in `FDFParser` and [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`PDFParser`.[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - A libFuzzer invocation on the PDFBox codebase timed out, indicating that the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzz harness did not complete within the allotted time.  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No stack trace or exception was produced beyond the “ERROR: libFuzzer: [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtimeout” message.[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Observations from the Patch Attempt  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The patch deletes existing public constructors in `COSParser` and replaces [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthem with private header-scanning routines.  [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Two new methods are added to `COSParser`:  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • `[0m[1;35mparsePDFHeader[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, which scans up to `headerLookupRange` bytes for the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstandard PDF header sequence,  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • `[0m[1;35mparseFDFHeader[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, which does the same for an FDF header.  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The new methods rely on a field `headerLookupRange` and constants [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`PDF_[0m[1;33mHEAD[0m[39mER`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`FDF_[0m[1;33mHEAD[0m[39mER`, neither of which are declared or initialized in the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mshown diff.  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - An import duplication [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets` appears twice[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m was [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mintroduced.[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Compilation Errors After Applying the Patch  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `COSParser.java`:  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • “method [0m[1;35mparsePDFHeader[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is already defined” and “method [0m[1;35mparseFDFHeader[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39malready defined” → methods collide with existing definitions.  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • “cannot find symbol: variable headerLookupRange” at two call sites → the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfield is not declared.  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `FDFParser.java`:  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Constructor call to `[0m[1;35mCOSParser[0m[1;39m([0m[39mRandomAccessRead[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` fails because the required[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msignature now expects five parameters.  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • “cannot find symbol: method [0m[1;35mparseFDFHeader[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m” → the method is either private[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mor missing from this class.  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `PDFParser.java`:  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Calls to `[0m[1;35mparsePDFHeader[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;35mparseFDFHeader[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` are unresolved, [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindicating these methods are not visible or not present.[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `COSParser` class:  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Verify existing definitions of `[0m[1;35mparsePDFHeader[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;35mparseFDFHeader[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Locate or declare `headerLookupRange` and confirm constants for header [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpatterns.  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Constructor signatures in `COSParser`:  [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Ensure backward compatibility for `FDFParser` and `PDFParser` usages.  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `FDFParser` and `PDFParser` classes:  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Audit calls to newly refactored methods and constructors to align with the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mupdated API.  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Import statements:  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Clean up duplicate imports and confirm use of `StandardCharsets`.[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
